<h2>PCS Internship Program</h2>
<hr>

<div class="container content-margin">

  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>
        By far, the most exciting part of my job is when one of our graduates tells me about getting hired!
      </h3>
      <p>
        After spending nearly 20 years in the Education field, I now have the good fortune of witnessing adult professionals enter our school with one set of skills, and leave well-equipped with a brand new set of skills.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether they are called 'interns' or 'junior devs' makes no never mind to them. They are bubbling with excitement about starting a brand new career in the exciting field of we development!
      </p>
      <%= mail_to "ckelly@portlandcodeschool.com", "Intern Me!", :class=>"btn btn-default big-apply-button", :subject=>"PCS Internship Program", :body=>"I am considering hiring a PCS graduate as an intern. Please contact me to discuss the details?" %>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <br>
      <%= image_tag "/images/intern_photo.jpg", :class=>"img-responsive" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>
        What you can expect from graduates of our Full Stack JavaScript classes
      </h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Nearly 500 hours of object-oriented programming in JavaScript</li>
        <li>Node on the back end</li>
        <li>Ember or Backbone on the front end</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL for db</li>
        <li>GitHub for version control</li>
        <li>Ability and desire to learn new technologies</li>
        <li>A positive, contributing member of your team</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>
        What is expected from the internship
      </h3>
      <br>
      <ul>
        <li>2 or 3 months in duration</li>
        <li>Paid position (at your company's intern wages)</li>
        <li>20-40 hours per week</li>
        <li>A healthy onboarding process</li>
        <li>Beer. Lots of beer.</li>
        <li>Respectful office culture</li>
        <li>Contributing member of the team</li>
        <li>Just kidding about the beer</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>

